Saving Throw: none

When this spell is cast, a jet of chilling frost shoots from the caster's fingertips, in jets of 5 ft. length in a horizontal arc of about 120 degrees in front of the caster. Any creature in the area receives 1d6 points of cold damage, plus 1 additional point for each three levels of the caster (to a maximum of 1d6+6 damage).
~
@7181  = ~Chromatic Orb~
@7182  = ~Chromatic Orb
(Evocation)

Level: 1
Range: 90 ft.
Duration: Special
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: Special

This spell causes a colorful sphere to appear in the caster's hand. When thrown, the sphere heads unerringly to its target. The effect the orb varies. Each orb will do damage to the target against which there is no save, and can trigger a secondary effect against which the target must save vs. Spell with a +2 bonus:
 20% chance: 1d4 damage and blinds the target for 1 round.
 20% chance: 1d4 damage and inflicts pain (-1 penalty to Strength, Dexterity, AC, and THAC0) upon the target.
 20% chance: 1d4 damage and stuns the target for 1 round.
 20% chance: 1d4 damage and causes weakness (-4 penalty to THAC0) in the target for 5 rounds.
 20% chance: 1d4 damage and panics the target for 2 rounds.
~
@7191  = ~Larloch's Minor Drain~
@7192  = ~Larloch's Minor Drain 
(Necromancy)

Level: 1
Range: 30 ft.
Duration: Special
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: None

With this spell, the wizard drains the life force from a target and adds it to <PRO_HISHER> own. The target creature suffers 2d3 damage (save vs. Death for half damage), while the caster gains 4 hit points. If the caster goes over <PRO_HISHER> maximum hit point total with this spell, <PRO_HESHE> loses any extra hit points after 1 turn.

A caster may only benefit from the extra hit points provided by this spell once per turn, regardless how many victims are drained, or how quickly.
~
@7241  = ~Wild Surge~
@7242  = ~Wild Surge
(Invocation/Evocation)

Level: 1
Range: Special
Duration: Special
Casting Time: Special
Area of Effect: Special
Saving Throw: Special

This is less a spell than a release of pure wild energy. Magic energy surrounds wild mages and courses through them. This effect is what happens if a wild mage loses control and allows such energy to be unleashed. There is no spell, no intended form the magic takes; only pure, random, magical manifestation.

Wild mages may release this energy at any time, as often as they like; but most spend their careers learning how to prevent it happening, rather than how to make it happen.
~
@7251  = ~Spook~
@7252  = ~Spook
(Illusion/Phantasm)

Level: 1
Range: 30 ft.
Duration: 3 rounds
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: Neg.

A Spook spell enables the wizard to play upon natural fears to cause the target creature to perceive the caster as someone or something inimical, which then appears to advance upon it in a threatening manner. If the creature does not make a successful Saving Throw vs. Spell, it turns and flees at maximum speed as far from the wizard as possible. The creature suffers a Saving Throw penalty of -1 every 2 levels of the caster, up to a maximum of -6 at 12th level. Although the caster does not actually pursue the fleeing creature, a phantasm from its own mind does. Undead are completely unaffected.

Anyone who has been the target of this spell - whether they make their saving throw or not - will be suspicious for a time, and cannot be affected by it for 8 hours. 
~

@7101  = ~Identify~
@7102  = ~Identify

Level: 1
School: Divination
Range: Caster
Duration: 3 rounds
Casting Time: 2
Area of Effect: Special
Saving Throw: None 

The caster of this spell gains a temporary insight into the history and nature of magical objects. This translates into a temporary Lore bonus of 20 points, plus an additional 20 points for each five levels of experience the caster has attained. If the resulting score is high enough, the spell can identify the name, nature, and function of any magical items in the caster's possession.
~


